Operation Molot (Hammer)

Date: May 1981

Time Limit: 21 turns

Briefing:

Comrade General, your presence here is no accident. High Command believes you possess the skill and determination to execute a mission of critical importance. The question is whether you can meet their expectations—or mine. This is no ordinary assignment. This is a test, both of your resolve and your ability to deliver victory for the Motherland.

Moscow has directed substantial resources to the region, forming the new 2nd Guards Army. You will be given command of its vanguard forces—use them wisely, as these units will form the core of your future operations. The Politburo's attention is divided; there are whispers of escalating tensions in Europe, but for now, your focus must remain absolute on the task at hand.

The Khost-Gardez Pass has been closed by insurgent activity. Ambushes and sabotage have turned this vital supply route into a kill zone. The Khost Islamic Liberation Front, led by Yousef Khan, coordinates these attacks from heavily fortified bases in the mountains along the pass and in the Khost Valley foothills. Your second objective is the Ghulam Khan Road, which runs parallel to the Pakistani border. This route serves as the Mujahedeen's primary resupply artery, funneling weapons and reinforcements from external supporters. Intelligence indicates their operations are coordinated from a major base along this road. Destroying it will cripple their logistics network.
Khost remains secure and provides access to two airbases that will serve as your operational hubs. These facilities offer reconnaissance, air support, and resupply capabilities.

Your mission objectives:

Eliminate Mujahedeen presence along the Khost-Gardez Pass.
Secure the Ghulam Khan Road.
Reclaim all villages under insurgent control.
Destroy the two enemy strongholds.

The Khost Islamic Liberation Front has controlled this region for too long. You have 21 days to restore Soviet authority. High Command is watching. Failure will have consequences. Dismissed.